xml

Interface IXMLFormat

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IRequirementAnalysis
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CustomXMLFormat, RequirementsInterchangeFormat

    public interface IXMLFormat
extends IRequirementAnalysis
    Interface for requirement analysis classes that provide XML conversion support. This interface is implemented by every requirement analysis class that provides XML conversion support. This is needed to make import and export methods generic and provide more flexibility. The createFragments(IRequirementAnalysis) method is used to convert the original data into the new requirement analysis format whoch provides XML conversion support. The interface extends the IRequirementAnalysis to make this XML conversion supporting classes also available via the interface of the IRequirementAnalysis.

    1.0
